parameters:
Chancellor Shif "Hehehe... Finally, the altar of Kusechirei and the shrine
maiden will be in my hands..."

Chancellor Shif "Thank you very much, General. Consider it an honor to
serve as one of my pawns in battle."
General Toros "Ye...s... I am most... grateful for this... happiness."

Chancellor Shif "Hehehe... Even General Toros, known for his valor, is
nothing but a puppet under my hypnotic magic... Well, it did take a
considerable amount of magic power and time, so make sure you work
accordingly..."
Soldier "Chancellor Shif! All troops are ready to deploy!"
Chancellor Shif "Yes, yes... then go ahead and trample them."

Chancellor Shif "Sigh... With this, I can finally say goodbye to those
annoying commoners... Well, whether they're commoners or nobles, it makes
no difference to me..."
Chancellor Shif "Well, it's about time to wrap things up, isn't it?"

Chancellor Shif "Ah, yes, yes, let's pull out quickly! Let's go back for a
meal."

Soldier "No, Lord Shif... that is... the First Division has... been
annihilated!"

Chancellor Shif "What?! That's impossible! There's no way that village has
such military power!"
Soldier "No... it was almost entirely done by Kru, the Swordmaster alone!"
Chancellor Shif "What! Such a thing... such a thing..."
General Tros "Hehehe... heh... hehe... heh... hahaha!"

Chancellor Shif "Tch! We can't have a discussion with weaklings! Deploy the
elite troops and eliminate them quickly!"
Chancellor Shif "Grr! Damn it! That damned commoner!"
General Tros "To perish... you too... and me... hehehe..."

Chancellor Shif "Be silent! You're just a puppet! Tch! ...However, no
matter how strong that commoner may be, there's no way he can handle an
elite troop after facing an entire division..."

Chancellor Shif "Haa... I'm getting impatient... I want to see Kru's face
torn to shreds already..."
Chancellor Shif "Ah! I've been waiting! Have you finished off Kru?!"
Soldier "No... we were completely wiped out!"

Chancellor Shif "What do you mean, wiped out! They are our nation's elite
troops!"
Chancellor Shif "Ahh! It's time for our last resort..."
Chancellor Shif "Ugh... Isn't it over yet!"
Chancellor Shif (This... this isn't how it was supposed to be...)
Chancellor Shif "What?! Have you taken care of that commoner?!"
Soldier "No! The enemy is approaching our main camp!"

Chancellor Shif "You ingrates! After all the kingdom has done for you...
you repay us with betrayal!"
Kru "What's this... Such cliché lines to start with. Boring."
Chancellor Shif "Silence! Tros! Finish this quickly!"

Chancellor Shif "Such... impossible... To think even Tros has been
defeated..."
Kru "Well... all that's left is your head..."

Chancellor Shif "Eek! Wait, wait! Calm down! Let's talk this out! Woman!
You wanted to make a deal with our country, right? I'll personally take
care of it!"

Kru "Huh? What sleepy talk are you spouting... Do you have any idea how
many soldiers and villagers have been hurt because of you?"
Kru "Your head alone is too cheap a price."

Chancellor Shif "Eek! I'm so sorry! I was only following the king's orders,
I had no choice..."

Kru "Either way, you're the one in charge of this battlefield. Without your
head, things won't settle down."
Chancellor Shif (No choice... if it's come to this...)
Umi "Good... this will save the village..."

Kru "Quickly order a full retreat for all troops! And tell the king to
never come near this forest again!"

Having lost their command tower, the kingdom's army retreated swiftly. We
watched them leave, then re-established the barrier and declared the end of
the war. With the tension finally broken, people began to cry in relief,
embrace each other, or laugh together, each celebrating the end of the war
in their own way.
